File: The Grahamstown High court ordered the council speaker to elect a mayor within seven days. Wikimedia Commons PORT ELIZABETH - The Nelson Mandela Bay Municipality will finally get a mayor on Tuesday. The metro has been without a mayor since 2019. READ: Bobani booted as Nelson Mandela Bay mayor This was after the late Mongameli Bobani was removed through a vote of no confidence. The Grahamstown High court ordered the council speaker to elect a mayor within seven days.